HEADWORD: Punto
<hw>Pun"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>punto</ets>,
L. <ets>punctum</ets> point. See <er>Point</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Fencing)</fld> <def>A point or hit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>\'d8Punto diritto</b></col> <ety>[It.]</ety>, <cd>a
direct stroke or hit.</cd> -- <col><b>\'d8Punto reverso</b></col>
<ety>[It. <ets>riverso</ets> reverse]</ety>, <cd>a backhanded
stroke.</cd> <au>Halliwell.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Ah, the immortal passado! the
<xex>punto reverso</xex>!⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

